<p>Here we see the most famous fractal in mathematics - the Mandelbrot set, which we found by a simple mathematical rule. The axes on Figure&nbsp;1 denote the real and imaginary parts of the complex number <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?c=a+bi"> where <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?a"> is the real value on the x axis and <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?b"> is the imaginary value on the y axis .</p>
<p><sup>[1]</sup> Magnitude of a complex number <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?z=a+bi"> is defined as <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%5Csqrt%7Ba%5E2+b%5E2%7D"></p>
